\section{Projects}

\subsection{Seven Segment Display Decoder for hexadecimal numbers -- FPGA}
\cvitem{}{ Designing and implementing a decoder for displaying hexadecimal numbers in seven segment displays using modelsim Altera suit, VHDL and Altera DE2 development board with Cyclone -- II FPGA. }

\subsection{4bit ALU -- FPGA }
\cvitem{}{Designing and implementing a 4bit ALU from scratch using modelsim/VHDL and test it using modelsim simulations and the Altera DE2 development board.}

\section{Projects}
\subsection{Android Custom Rom}
\cvitem{}{Building a Android Custom Rom (Custom Android version) for HTC Desire HD mobile phone directly from AOSP ( Android Open Source Project).\newline
The process of porting a new version of Android (4.2.2 JellyBean in this case) to a legacy hardware platform consist of several steps like picking the right source trees from various git and some other kinds of source repositories, picking the right linux drivers (kernel modules) from the hardware venders, initialize and configure the local android build system with the sources and drivers chosen above according to device specification, downloading the sources using android build system, building android from source, debugging the build on real hardware, fixing the bugs and rebuild until a usable stability is reached.
\newline
The process of building Android itself gives a great deal of understanding about Android build system, version control systems like git, Linux internals and the hardware platform.}

\subsection{Porting FirefoxOS (B2G) to a new hardware platform}
\cvitem{}{Porting FirefoxOS, otherwise known as Boot to Gecko (B2G) to HTC Desire HD hardware includes most of the android porting steps and additionally includes the process of building customized gecko version optimized mobile phones and touch screens on top of the Android sources. Then a custom kernel optimized for \newline FirefoxOS should be built and the build should be debugged on real hardware until a usable stability is reached.
}

\subsection{User level thread library -- C}
\cvitem{}{Designing and implementing of context switching library for user level C programmes which requires the basic knowledge about synchronization, process scheduling algorithms, x86 hardware architecture assembly and C calling conventions for x86.}

\subsection{Virtual Memory Management System -- OS161}
\cvitem{}{Designing and implementing a Virtual Memory Management System for educational operating system OS161 requires the knowledge about basic virtual memory concepts like paging, page tables, swapping and also the knowledge about synchronization primitives and basic hardware knowledge about how the physical memory (RAM, ROM) works. 
\newline
This also gives the confidence to work with large code bases (over 8000 loc) and lot of understanding about low level C coding and UNIX internals.  }

\subsection{Building Linux From Scratch -- LFS 7.5}
\cvitem{}{Linux From Scratch is a comprehensive book about how to build a own customizable Linux system from scratch which lets the user to gain the knowledge about how Linux works internally from booting to x-windows systems.}

\subsection{Car park management system -- Java}
\cvitem{}{Car park management system which lets the user to mange a car park with full fledged GUI which uses MySQL as the database system.}

\section{Projects}
\subsection{OCR based chemical reaction solver -- Android}
\cvitem{}{An android mobile application which uses Google's tesseract OCR engine to identify a chemical reaction printed on a paper and return the result.}

\subsection{HTML Tag Cloud Generator -- C}
\cvitem{}{UNIX based HTML Tag Cloud genarator which takes advantage of UNIX multiprocessing architecture and syscalls to speed up the processing of a large number of HTML files concurrently.}

\subsection{Automated Timetable -- Android}
\cvitem {}{Automated android timetable which synchronize across multiple people and devices with the help of the Google calender API and PhoneGap to keep in track with academic timetable changes and updates, notices, etc...}

\subsection{Online Fashion Store -- PHP, MySQL}
\cvitem{}{Online Fashion which a user can order fashion items with a adminstration panel for administrative staff based on PHP and MySQL as the database backend. }

\subsection{Singlish for Mobile -- JavaME}
\cvitem{}{Singlish text to Unicode Sinhala text converter for low end JavaME compatible mobile phones}




